---
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQAccordion from '../components/FAQAccordion.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import SupportPanel from '../components/SupportPanel.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Do I need a referral?',
    answer: 'No referral is required. You can contact Marie directly.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How long is a session?',
    answer: 'Sessions are usually around 50 minutes. If you need a different format, please ask.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you offer online appointments?',
    answer: 'In-person sessions are available in Kanturk, Co. Cork. If online appointments would suit you better, please ask when you get in touch.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is what I say confidential?',
    answer: 'Confidentiality is taken very seriously. Any limits are explained clearly at the start so you know where you stand.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you work with teenagers?',
    answer: 'Support for children and young people is available. Please ask about age suitability and what kind of support may be most appropriate.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What if I am nervous about the first session?',
    answer: 'That is very common. You are not expected to explain everything at once. The first session is simply a starting point.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I cancel or rearrange?',
    answer: 'Please give as much notice as possible if you need to cancel or move an appointment. Full practical details are on the Fees and cancellations page.'
  }
];
---

<Layout
  title="How Counselling Works | Marie Harding"
  description="A clear guide to starting counselling with Marie Harding in Kanturk, Co. Cork, including first sessions, confidentiality, online options, and practical details."
  canonicalPath="/how-counselling-works"
>
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <Breadcrumbs
      items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'How counselling works' }
      ]}
    />
    <PageHeader
      title="How counselling works"
      intro="Counselling should feel clear and manageable. This page explains what happens before the first session, what sessions are like, and the practical details people often want to know."
    />
  </div>

  <section class="soft-panel mt-8 px-6 py-6 md:px-8">
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-800">
      You do not need to know exactly what to say before you make contact. A few lines, or a simple phone call to ask about availability, is enough to begin.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-grid mt-8 xl:grid-cols-4">
    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="section-kicker">Before you attend</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">First contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">You can get in touch by phone or email to ask about availability, timing, and whether the support feels suitable for you.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="section-kicker">The first appointment</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">A calm starting point</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">The first session is a chance to talk through what has brought you in, what you need, and how support may begin.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="section-kicker">Ongoing sessions</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Clear and practical</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">Sessions can stay focused on what matters most to you, with space to review what is helping and what needs attention next.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="feature-card">
      <p class="section-kicker">Practical details</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">No hidden uncertainty</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">You can ask about format, timing, cancellations, and any practical concern before you commit to ongoing work.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="service-layout mt-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem]">
    <article class="prose-safe">
      <h2>What happens before the first session</h2>
      <p>
        When you get in touch, the first step is usually a short conversation about what kind of support you are looking for,
        what times may suit, and whether the service feels like the right fit.
      </p>
      <p>
        You are welcome to keep that first contact simple. You do not need to tell your full story straight away.
      </p>

      <h2>What the first session is like</h2>
      <p>
        The first session is a starting point rather than a test. We talk about what has brought you in,
        what feels most important right now, and what you hope counselling may provide.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some people arrive knowing exactly what they want to discuss. Others feel unsure or find it hard to put things into words at first.
        Both are completely normal.
      </p>

      <h2>Confidentiality and its limits</h2>
      <p>
        Confidentiality is of the utmost importance to me when working with clients.
        If there are any legal or safety-related limits to confidentiality, these are explained clearly at the start so you know where you stand.
      </p>

      <h2>In-person and online options</h2>
      <p>
        In-person sessions are available in Kanturk, Co. Cork.
        If online appointments would suit you better, please ask when you get in touch.
      </p>

      <h2>How often sessions may happen</h2>
      <p>
        Session timing can be discussed together.
        Some people prefer regular appointments, while others need more space between sessions.
        What matters is choosing a rhythm that feels realistic and supportive.
      </p>

      <h2>Cancellations and practical expectations</h2>
      <p>
        If you need to cancel or rearrange, please give as much notice as possible.
        Full practical details are on the <a href="/fees-and-cancellations">Fees and cancellations</a> page,
        and anything unclear can be discussed before booking.
      </p>

      <h2>If you are nervous about attending</h2>
      <p>
        Many people feel uneasy before a first session, especially if counselling is new to them.
        You are not expected to say everything perfectly, and there is no pressure to cover everything at once.
      </p>
      <p>
        The aim is to create a calm space where it feels easier to begin.
      </p>

      <h2>Emergency care</h2>
      <p>
        This practice is not an emergency or crisis service.
        If you need urgent help, call 112 or 999. Samaritans freephone 116 123.
      </p>
    </article>

    <aside class="service-sidebar space-y-4">
      <section class="soft-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">At a glance</p>
        <ul class="mini-list mt-4">
          <li>First contact can be by phone or email.</li>
          <li>The first session is a calm starting point.</li>
          <li>Confidentiality is taken very seriously.</li>
          <li>In-person sessions are available in Kanturk, Co. Cork.</li>
          <li>Please ask if online appointments would suit you better.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="soft-panel">
        <p class="section-kicker">Useful next steps</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm font-medium">
          <a class="link-subtle" href="/contact">Request an appointment</a>
          <a class="link-subtle" href="/fees-and-cancellations">Fees and cancellations</a>
          <a class="link-subtle" href="/about-marie">About Marie</a>
          <a class="link-subtle" href="/resources">Support resources</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section-shell mt-14 px-6 py-8 md:px-8 md:py-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="section-kicker">Frequently asked questions</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 md:text-3xl">Practical questions, answered clearly</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-8">
      <FAQAccordion items={faqs} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mt-14">
    <SupportPanel intro="If you need urgent help, or if you would find additional support useful alongside counselling, these official services may help." />
  </div>
</Layout>
